  "text": "It is clear that S. pneumoniae is the most frequently identified pathogen causing CAP and that high-level penicillin resistance may not be as high as presumed [CITATION_1] . Therefore data from Cambodia, Thailand and Vietnam suggest that amoxicillin probably remains a valid option for empirical treatment of CAP. Instead, S. pneumoniae displayed high levels (,75%) of resistance to trimethoprim/sulfamethoxazole in all studies from Cambodia, Thailand and Vietnam included in this review precluding its empirical use for CAP. A close surveillance of resistance patterns in S. pneumoniae is highly warranted.",
